Package edu.harvard.data.generator Description

This package contains the code generator that builds Java classes, as well as Bash and SQL scripts that correspond to a dataset schema. The code in this package is explicitly not tied to any particular data set. The intent is that any dataset-specific code is factored out to a dataset-specific caller.

The main interfaces to this package are the GenerationSpec and CodeGenerator classes. A client of this code should create a subtype of CodeGenerator to manage the generation process, and should populate a SchemaTransformer with DataSchema instances representing each required processing phase, along with the additional data such as Java packages or class prefixes that will be required to generate a standard set of files. See the documentation for GenerationSpec for details of the parameters that are required.

Once the caller has build the GenerationSpec object, the various generators can then be invoked. See the documentation for each generator for the files that it creates. By convention generators in this package have the suffix "Generator".

The Java code generator is more complex than the generators for other scripts, and so is split into multiple generator classes. The entry point to the Java generator is JavaBindingGenerator .
